## 2. Mandatory Conventions

### 2.1 File Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|:-----|:--------|:--------|
| Permanent note | `Declarative-Title.md` | `HTTP-methods-define-request-semantics.md` |
| Literature note | `LIT-Source-Title.md` | `LIT-Fielding-REST-Dissertation.md` |
| Fleeting note | `FLEET-Brief-Title.md` | `FLEET-API-design-thoughts.md` |
| Study plan | `[ContextName]-Study-Plan.md` | `RestAPIs-Study-Plan.md` |
| Context folders | PascalCase, no spaces | `MachineLearning`, `WebSecurity` |

### 2.2 Declarative Titles

Titles MUST be complete statements in **Subject-Verb-Object** format:

- âœ… `HTTP-methods-define-request-semantics`
- âœ… `Encapsulation-hides-internal-object-state-from-external-access`
- âŒ `HTTP Methods` (vague, not declarative)
- âŒ `Introduction to APIs` (generic)

### 2.3 Tags â€” `#CONTEXT-REFERENCE` Format

- PascalCase in both components
- Minimum 3, maximum 7 tags per permanent note
- Tag 1: primary context Â· Tag 2: conceptual category Â· Tag 3+: cross-references

```
#AWS-EventDriven  #Architecture-Microservices  #Python-AsyncIO
#DataStructures-BinaryTrees  #Security-OAuth2  #Frontend-ReactHooks
```

### 2.4 Internal Links

- Exclusive format: WikiLinks `[[Note-Title]]`
- Never use markdown links `[text](link)`
- Prerequisites: declared at the beginning of the note
- Related concepts: declared at the end of the note
- Embedded diagrams: `![[diagram-name]]`

### 2.5 Diagrams â€” Mermaid Only

| Purpose | Mermaid Type |
|:--------|:-------------|
| Concept dependencies | `flowchart` |
| Study plan sequence | `flowchart` or `timeline` |
| Knowledge graphs | `graph` |
| Mind maps | `mindmap` |
| Class relationships | `classDiagram` |

