## 5. Vault Generation Process

### 5.1 Step 1 â€” Initialization

1. Create directory structure per Â§1.1
2. Copy `.obsidian/` from the repository
3. Create `00-INDEX/Master-Index.md` and `00-INDEX/Context-Map.md` (empty, with placeholders)

### 5.2 Step 2 â€” Context Definition

- Define context name in PascalCase (e.g., `MachineLearning`, `WebSecurity`)
- Create folder at `10-CONTEXTS/[ContextName]/` with subfolders `permanent-notes/`, `literature-notes/`, `fleeting-notes/`

### 5.3 Step 3 â€” Atomic Decomposition

Follow the methodology defined in `.zettelkasten` to decompose the subject into atomic concepts. Generate table:

| Seq | Declarative Title | Description (50â€“100 words) | Prerequisites | Bloom Level | Tags |
|:----|:------------------|:---------------------------|:--------------|:------------|:-----|
| 1 | [Subject-Verb-Object] | [Why it matters + application] | None | understand | #Ctx-Ref1 #Ctx-Ref2 |
| 2 | [Subject-Verb-Object] | [Why it matters + application] | [[note-1]] | apply | #Ctx-Ref1 #Ctx-Ref2 |

### 5.4 Step 4 â€” Dependency Graph

Create Mermaid `flowchart TD` diagram showing the learning path with prerequisites. Use colors per phase:
- Foundations: `fill:#e1f5ff`
- Structural Concepts: `fill:#d4edda`
- Application: `fill:#fff4e1`
- Analysis & Integration: `fill:#f8d7da`
- Creation: `fill:#ffe1e1`

### 5.5 Step 5 â€” Permanent Note Generation

For each atomic concept:
1. Create file `Declarative-Title.md` in `10-CONTEXTS/[ContextName]/permanent-notes/`
2. Apply template Â§3.2
3. Fill `bloom_level` field in frontmatter
4. Include prerequisite and related concept links
5. Include 3â€“7 tags in `#CONTEXT-REFERENCE` format

### 5.6 Step 6 â€” Study Plan Document

Create `20-STUDY-PLANS/[ContextName]-Study-Plan.md` applying template Â§4.3.

### 5.7 Step 7 â€” Index Updates

