## 8. Common Mistakes â€” Avoid

| # | Mistake | Correction |
|:--|:--------|:-----------|
| 1 | Notes covering multiple concepts | SPLIT into separate notes |
| 2 | Vague titles ("Introduction to X") | USE Subject-Verb-Object statements |
| 3 | Missing prerequisites | ALWAYS declare dependencies |
| 4 | More than 7 tags per note | KEEP focused and relevant |
| 5 | Orphaned notes (no links) | CONNECT to the knowledge graph |
| 6 | Non-Mermaid diagrams | USE Mermaid exclusively |
| 7 | Markdown links `[text](link)` | USE WikiLinks `[[note]]` |
| 8 | Notes outside `10-CONTEXTS/` | ORGANIZE in the correct folder |
| 9 | Context missing from Master Index | ALWAYS update |
| 10 | Generic tags (`#programming`) | USE specific `#Context-Reference` format |
| 11 | Flat topic list in study plan | STRUCTURE by cognitive progression (Bloom) |
| 12 | Circular dependencies | ENSURE DAG structure |

